= Step Blocks

Step blocks are used to create numbered step-by-step instructions.

== Basic Steps

[step]
====
Step 1: First action

This is the first step in the process.
====

[step]
====
Step 2: Second action

This is the second step.
====

[step]
====
Step 3: Third action

This is the third step.
====

== Steps with Titles

[step]
====
.Title: Initialize Project
Create a new project directory and initialize it.
====

[step]
====
.Title: Install Dependencies
Install all required dependencies.
====

[step]
====
.Title: Configure Settings
Set up configuration files.
====

== Steps with Multiple Paragraphs

[step]
====
Step with multiple paragraphs.

Here's the second paragraph.

And a third paragraph with more details.
====

== Steps with Lists

[step]
====
Step with a list:

* First item
* Second item
* Third item
====

== Steps with Code

[step]
====
Step with code block:

[source]
----
npm install
----
====

